[[File:Rancho.jpg|thumb|250px|Rancho Obi-Wan]]
'''Rancho Obi-Wan''' is the [[Wikipedia:Sonoma County, California|Sonoma County, California]] residence and storehouse of [[Stephen J. Sansweet]], where he maintains the world's largest private ''[[Star Wars]]'' collection. It is covered in the online video [[Visit to Rancho Obi-Wan]]. It was featured as the site of an auction in the premiere episode of [[Wikipedia:Syfy|SyFy's]] series ''Collection Intervention''. At the end of the episode, Sansweet himself bought a life-size replica of [[Clone trooper captain|Captain]] [[Rex/Legends|Rex]] from ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]''.<ref>[http://www.syfy.com/collectionintervention ''Collection Intervention''] - SyFy.com</ref> Its content was presented at [[2012]]'s [[Celebration VI]] and at [[2019]]'s [[Celebration Chicago]].<ref>{{SW|url=news/swcvi-packing-up-the-rancho-and-taking-it-on-the-road|text=SWCVI: Packing up the Rancho and taking it on the road}}</ref><ref>{{SW|url=news/rancho-obi-wan-star-wars-celebration-chicago|text=Rancho Obi-Wan Coming to ''Star Wars'' Celebration Chicago}}</ref>

